<br>
for example: in one of my story's that is partially based on dbz there is a boy that, after a long battle, sacrifices himself to blow up a planet that threatens earth (the alien planet can deflect KI blasts so the sacrifice was necisary). His girlfriend/lover stays on earth and cries for her lost friend/lover. An huge cloud of interstellar dust hangs over the place where the alien planet first was. When the dust clears the girl can see that the alien planet is stil intact. The girl now has a target for her anger and with a screem of pain she, a human, goes super and charges a huge energiewave. While she fires the wave she shouts his lover's name out loud and the wave gains even more power. (I know, it's a little old but it is NOT the final battle) The wave penitrates every defence the alien planet knows and blows it to smitheries. <br>
<br>
Now think of how the emotions in the face of the girl could tell every bit of history she had with her lover. The pain she feels mixed with the anger towards the alien planet that pushes her over the limit. <br>
<br>
Even though I have written better action scenes, I thought that you guys/girls could picture this easier. <br>
<br>
I just love the feeling when a story or movie makes me think: &quot;He's really gonna feel it now&quot; or &quot;Big mistake.&quot;<br>
<br>
I only have two more things to say:<br>
one: I agree with people that say you shouldn't strech a fight if you can't make it interesting anymore. But if you only have written ten lines it should better be a very unimportant fight.<br>
two: sorry if my English sucks but I'm from Holland so please spare me.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=soulx5k>soulx5k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/20/02 5:49:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What makes a good battle??????</span><hr size=1> A good thing that makes the battle good is when you find that your enemy is just as good as you and that his moves and abilities are impressive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=soulx5k>soulx5k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/20/02 5:50:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What makes a good battle??????</span><hr size=1> A good thing that makes the battle good is when you find that your enemy is just as good as you and that his moves and abilities are impressive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=soulx5k>soulx5k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/20/02 5:54:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index