Don't extend a person's fighting potential more than you should. Not everyone has a black belt in karate.    <br>
<br>
Purpose is definately a big factor in a fight, whether it be animated or not. Also, the PEOPLE engaged in the fight are very important. For example, a fight would mean more if it were between a father and son than if it were between a guy and some thug. <br>
<br>
I hate to pick on DBZ (since I USED to be a huge fan of it) but I also despise when fights are long and drawn out more than necessary. You know what I mean. I'm sure that it's a guy thing, but 20+ episode-long fights can become rather tiring after a while. <p><b>Niea loves you.</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=themamba2>TheMamba2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/23/02 9:32:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What makes a good battle??????</span><hr size=1> evangelion, you make a good point. I can't stand watching a fight if I know the outcome or what someone is oging to do next. Every episode of sailor moon ends with some crystal magic fire heart love power blast crap and it gets reeeeeeeeeeeeally annoying, even if its the first time you've seen it. The thing about signature moves that have to be &quot;charged up&quot; over a period of more than one second would never work in a real fight. Your opponent is going to run over and start beating the crap out of you as soon as you begin the &quot;charge up&quot; if s/he has half a brain. actually, you don't even need half a brain to realize that when you're in a fight, you don't take a frickin break while whoever it is you're fighting does a little coreographed dance/hand motion/meditation. YOU KEEP ON FIGHTING (der, really?). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=niea7>niea7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/23/02 10:22:29 pm)</font><br>   <a